\deflang1033\pard\plain\f3\fs17 NOTES
\par \bullet  Reaction dependent on serum magnesium concentration 
\par 
\par Indication:
\par \bullet  To test paroxysmal nocturnal haemoglobinuria (PNH) caused by abnormality of the red cell membrane 
\par SAMPLE REQUIREMENT
\par Serum
\par 
\par NORMAL VALUE
\par Negative
\par 
\par METHOD
\par \bullet  Haemolytic action of complement in acidified serum
\par 
\par CONDITIONS/DISEASES
\par 
\par Positive in:
\par \bullet  Paroxysmal nocturnal hemoglobinuria (PNH)
\par 
\par False positive in:
\par \bullet  Hereditary or acquired spherocytosis
\par \bullet  Recent transfusion with aged RBC
\par \bullet  Aplastic anemia
\par \bullet  Myeloproliferative syndromes
\par \bullet  Leukemia
\par \bullet  Hereditary dyserythropoietic anemia type II (HEMPAS)
\par 
\par Synonyms:
\par \bullet  Ham test
\par \bullet  Ham's acid lysis test
\par }
